race.comment: YES LULU (4) gave away a big start when she rounded them up with ridiculous at the big odds over 1400m at Rosehill in this grade last start. Will handle the weight rise and this could be a rinse and repeat. STARMAN (14) kept fresh when going to the front for a fighting second to YES LULU. Meets her better at the weights today and no surprise to see him push forward again from the low draw. Each way. MIDNIGHT DYNAMITE (6) back in trip when he speared across from the awkward gate to finish sixth over 1200m at Rosehill. Ready for the 1400m now but struggling to draw a decent gate. Keep safe. BARTOLF (8) holding his form and desperate for rain. Comes out of a strong form race and shapes as a leading each way player. EDITING (12) has needed both runs this time in, and improvement is anticipated over the 1400m. D-Day is looming.
